Key Match Events: Josh Hazlewood and Mitchell Starc shared the first three wickets
Brydon Carse and Adil Rashid each scored 26 and 27 respectively
Australia were reduced to 221 for nine
Miscellaneous Highlights: England suffered a 68-run loss to Australia
England is 2-0 down in the series with three matches remaining
Harry Brook's head fell across the line after being served an inswinger from Starc, with the review being declined
Travis Head and Matthew Short were dismissed for 29 each
Glenn Maxwell became Adil Rashid's 200th ODI wicket
Aaron Hardie and Will Jacks were dismissed
Australia were all out in 44.4 overs
